INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('174', '4', '2016-08-17 00:51:29', '2016-08-17 00:51:29', '<strong>MRC Luxury River Expeditions</strong>\r\n\r\nUnlike most other hotels, resorts and cruise ships, this is not “Our” exotic expedition - it is all ‘Yours’. It is not our manner to tell you what to do, when to do it, or how to enjoy yourselves. We are quite simply your facilitators, your guides, hosts &amp; hostesses. We are all focused and passionate about providing you with a heart-warming “Once in a Life-time” truly unique and exotic Asian adventure holiday. Welcome to Mekong River Cruiser.\r\n\r\nYes - we provide all ‘mod-cons’ and state of the art luxury, but you certainly expect that in a boutique five star environment nowadays. Yes - we present an array of room amenities and guest facilities that are second to none in the country, if not the region. So what makes us special..?\r\n\r\nHumbly, we offer our “guarantee of service”…. quiet, understated, efficient; discerning like you. And then again, those extra special touches that makes for that extra special attention to detail.\r\n\r\nAs Rudyard Kipling once said; “The trip, the journey, the fulfilment will be yours…”\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'About us', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2016-10-04 08:58:30', '2016-10-04 08:58:30', '', '0', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/?page_id=174', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('175', '4', '2016-08-17 00:47:06', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Once you have booked your next great adventure with Mekong River Cruiser (MRC), we invite you to review the Resources section of our website, which will provide you with all the information you need in preparing for your journey.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">PASSENGER INFORMATION FORMS</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In order to be fully compliant with certain foreign government and airline security regulations, Haimark must provide specific information to authorities on each guest booked on one of our cruises. Completed forms (one per guest) must be received prior to the release of final documents.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">PROGRAM GUIDES</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Guests who booked a combination land/cruise program will find our Program Guides helpful for information on both the land and cruise portions of their specific itinerary. Please download the program guide that is specifically designed for the tour you have booked.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">VISAS</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Many of our programs require visas to be obtained prior to departing your home country. Our visa partner will help ensure you receive the appropriate visas for your entire itinerary.</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">TRAVEL INSURANCE</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While Haimark does not require that guests purchase travel insurance, we highly recommend that guests ensure they are covered for unexpected medical and travel issues. Our travel insurance partner offers basic and comprehensive policies to accommodate the needs of most travelers. </span>', 'Before your go', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2016-08-17 00:47:06', '2016-08-17 00:47:06', '', '0', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/?p=175', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('176', '4', '2016-08-17 00:51:12', '2016-08-17 00:51:12', 'Once your reservation has been made with Mekong River Cruiser (MRC Ltd), we invite you to review the <em>Resources</em> section of the website, which will provides all the required information in readiness for your journey. Visit www.vietcruises.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPASSENGER INFORMATION FORMS\r\n\r\nIn order to be fully compliant with certain foreign government and airline security regulations, MRC Ltd must provide specific information to the authorities on each reservation. Completed forms (one per guest) must be received prior to the release of final documents.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPROGRAM GUIDES\r\n\r\nGuests who have reserved a combination of land &amp; cruise components will find our <em>Program Guides</em> offer an abundance of helpful information. Please download the program guide that is specifically designed for the travel components that you have selected.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nVISAS\r\n\r\nMany of our travel programs require visas to be obtained prior to departing from your home country. Our visa partner will ensure that you receive the appropriate visas for your entire itinerary.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTRAVEL INSURANCE\r\n\r\nMRC Ltd does not require that guests purchase travel insurance. However, we highly recommend insurance to cover for unexpected medical and general travel issues. Our travel insurance partner offers both basic and comprehensive policies to accommodate the needs of most travelers.', 'Before you go', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'before-you-go', '', '', '2016-10-11 09:18:35', '2016-10-11 09:18:35', '', '0', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/?page_id=176', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('177', '4', '2016-08-17 00:51:12', '2016-08-17 00:51:12', 'Once you have booked your next great adventure with Mekong River Cruiser (MRC), we invite you to review the Resources section of our website, which will provide you with all the information you need in preparing for your journey.\r\n\r\nPASSENGER INFORMATION FORMS\r\nIn order to be fully compliant with certain foreign government and airline security regulations, MRC must provide specific information to authorities on each guest booked on one of our cruises. Completed forms (one per guest) must be received prior to the release of final documents.\r\n\r\nPROGRAM GUIDES\r\nGuests who booked a combination land/cruise program will find our Program Guides helpful for information on both the land and cruise portions of their specific itinerary. Please download the program guide that is specifically designed for the tour you have booked.\r\n\r\nVISAS\r\nMany of our programs require visas to be obtained prior to departing your home country. Our visa partner will help ensure you receive the appropriate visas for your entire itinerary.\r\n\r\nTRAVEL INSURANCE\r\nMRC does not require that guests purchase travel insurance, we highly recommend that guests ensure they are covered for unexpected medical and travel issues. Our travel insurance partner offers basic and comprehensive policies to accommodate the needs of most travelers.', 'Before you go', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '176-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-17 00:51:12', '2016-08-17 00:51:12', '', '176', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/uncategorized/176-revision-v1-177.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('178', '4', '2016-08-17 00:51:29', '2016-08-17 00:51:29', '<strong>MRC Luxury River Expeditions</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For centuries, the world has been drawn to the legends and cultures of southern Asia, a cradle of nations with traditions and roots extending millennia.  India, Vietnam, Cambodia, Myanmar - their names alone evoke vivid images of places and people, art and architecture, and cuisines like none other in the world.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For each of these ancient civilizations, a river flows through its heart. The Irrawaddy bisects Myanmar - once called Burma - host to vibrant temples, pagodas, and villages, long closed to the West, that now invite exploration.  Vietnam and Cambodia, sustained by the mighty Mekong, blend colonial influences with long-standing tradition, spanning from the 12th-century Angkor Wat to the 20th-century Opera House in Ho Chi Minh City.  India, the legendary Ganges its lifeblood, has inspired writers and thinkers since long before Kipling, with a vibrancy that pulsates within this emerging economic powerhouse.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To experience such rich environments, only travel by river can provide the access, the pace, and the continuous beauty that they deserve.  Aboard one of MRC\'s exclusive river ships, you will venture into the soul of each storied setting, visiting cherished and iconic sites by day and enjoying 5-star hospitality and luxury by night.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Aboard the Irrawaddy Explorer, the Mekong Navigator, or the Ganges Voyager, you will enjoy the sanctity of a private suite and world-class dining-courtesy of Culinary Director, Chef Jorg Penneke-merged with premiere accommodations.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From an on-board spa featuring regional and Western treatments, to luxuriously appointed lounges where you can enjoy handcrafted cocktails, you will find your home on the water a retreat to relax and internalize the sights and sounds from each day\'s excursions on shore.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Experience Asia, experience <a href=\"http://www.vietcruises.com/\">MRC</a>.</strong>', 'About us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '174-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-17 00:51:29', '2016-08-17 00:51:29', '', '174', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/uncategorized/174-revision-v1-178.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('179', '4', '2016-08-17 00:59:55', '2016-08-17 00:59:55', '<strong>IMPORTANT NOTICE</strong>\r\n\r\nTerms and Conditions apply to all vessels under Viet Princess Cruises operation unless otherwise noted. Any and all information contained herein is in effect at the time of printing and is subject to change at any time. Information contained in this brochure does not form  INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('180', '4', '2016-08-17 00:59:55', '2016-08-17 00:59:55', '<strong>IMPORTANT NOTICE</strong>\r\nTerms and Conditions apply to all vessels under MRC Ltd. operation unless otherwise noted. Any and all information contained herein is in effect at the time of printing and is subject to change at any time.\r\nInformation contained in this brochure does not form INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('182', '4', '2016-08-17 05:09:28', '2016-08-17 05:09:28', 'Listed below are some of the more popular questions asked from guests booking our cruises. While the list is not exhaustive, you may find your questions answered here. Should you have additional questions we have not addressed, please feel free to contact us.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'FAQ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'faq', '', '', '2016-09-29 08:38:33', '2016-09-29 08:38:33', '', '0', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/?page_id=182', '0', 'page', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('183', '4', '2016-08-17 05:09:28', '2016-08-17 05:09:28', 'Listed below are some of the more popular questions asked from guests booking our cruises. While the list is not exhaustive, you may find your questions answered here. Should you have additional questions we have not addressed, please feel free to contact us.\r\n\r\nWhy should I choose a river cruise?\r\nHow are your cruises priced?\r\nDo I pay extra for excursions?\r\nHow do I pay for my cruise?\r\nWhat methods of payment do you accept for the cruise?\r\nWhat currencies are accepted for payment?\r\nWhat is your cancellation policy?\r\nIs there an age limit?\r\nAre MRC cruises handicapped accessible?\r\nDo I need a passport and visa to participate in your cruise programs?\r\nWill MRC help me with additional arrangements if I wish to extend my stay before and/or after the cruise?\r\nWhat information do I get before my cruise?\r\nWhat amenities are available on board?\r\nIs Internet available on the ships?\r\nCan I use my cell phone on board the ship?\r\nCan special diets be accommodated?\r\nDo I need travel insurance?\r\nAre there any luggage restrictions?\r\nWhat is the dress code during the cruise?\r\nWhat are the tipping guidelines for my cruise?\r\nCan I prepay my gratuities?\r\n\r\n<strong>Why should I choose a river cruise?</strong>\r\nOur guests have the opportunity to maximize how much of a country they can see, while only unpacking once in the most luxurious and spacious cabins on the rivers where we operate. One price includes all meals, excursions, English-speaking guides, and access into the must-see sites in every port.\r\n\r\n<strong>How are your cruises priced?</strong>\r\nOur cruise prices are listed per person, and based on double occupancy. Our cabins will accommodate single occupancy, at a supplement, which varies based on selected cabin category. Pricing is subject ot increase without notice, prior to booking your cruise, and does not include airfare, unless otherwise noted. A deposit of 25% is required to secure your space and the pricing of your cruise.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do I pay extra for excursions?</strong>\r\nWe have a wide variety of excursions that are included in the price of each cruise. In select ports, however, where there is an extended amount of free time and a wide variety of activities available, MRC cruises does provide a selection of Optional Excursions that guests may choose from to enhance their cruising experience.\r\n\r\n<strong>How do I pay for my cruise?</strong>\r\nYou may book directly through the MRC booking system, or you may contact your local travel agent. Should you wish to book directly, please click here.\r\n\r\n<strong>What methods of payment do you accept for the cruise?</strong>\r\nMRC accepts Visa, MasterCard, and Discover for both deposit and final payment.\r\n\r\n<strong>What currencies are accepted for payment?</strong>\r\nAll cruise payments, as well as all payments on board our ships, are made in US dollars only.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is your cancellation policy?</strong>\r\nIf it becomes necessary to cancel your cruise, written notification must be submitted to the MRC offices, and any cruise tickets that may have been issued must be returned before any refund that might be due is processed. Cancellation penalties below will be assessed when written cancellation is received within the following dates:\r\n\r\nBetween deposit and 120 days prior to cruise date: <strong>$850</strong> per person\r\nBetween 120 and 91 days prior to cruise date: <strong>50%</strong> of cruise price\r\nLess than 90 days prior to cruise date: <strong>100%</strong> of total cruise price\r\n\r\nIf you need to cancel pre- or post-land program extensions, the following penalties will be assessed when written cancellation is received within the following date periods:\r\nBetween 90 and 61 days prior to program start date: $250 per person\r\nBetween 60 days and program start date: 100% of total land program price\r\n\r\n<strong>Is there an age limit?</strong>\r\nDue to the nature of the countries in which we travel, MRC is unable to accommodate children under 12 years of age. While we have no maximum age limit, guests should be physically fit and able to climb in and out of sampans and excursion boats, and walk up (sometimes steep) hills in ports where docks are not available. MRC ships do not have elevators, and guests must be able to navigate multiple flights of steps.\r\n\r\n<strong>Are MRC cruises handicapped accessible?</strong>\r\nMRC ships are not handicapped accessible and do not have elevators. Many of the sites we visit have not been adapted to be handicapped accessible, nor have the transportation systems that are available in these areas. In most situations we are unable to provide individual assistance to travelers with mobility issues.\r\n\r\n<strong>Will MRC help me with additional arrangements if I wish to extend my stay before and/or after the cruise?</strong>\r\nMRC offers pre- and post-cruise land extensions to each of our cruises. Details of each extension are available in the Land Extensions section of the website, as well as within each ship’s information. MRC will also be pleased to assist you in extending your extension stay in our selected land program hotels.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do I need a passport and visa to participate in your cruise programs?</strong>\r\nWhenever traveling outside your home country, a passport is required. Some countries also require a visa. In order to determine if you need a visit to visit a specific country, you may visit an embassy website for the particular country, or contact our recommended visa service G3 Visas if you need assistance in obtaining your visa(s).\r\n\r\n<strong>What information do I get before my cruise?</strong>\r\nApproximately two weeks prior to departure, MRC will provide your final travel documents, which includes an itinerary, information on any land extensions booked, and any air tickets booked through us.\r\n\r\n<strong>What amenities are available on board?</strong>\r\nSome amenities vary by ship, but are listed in each ship’s information on the website.\r\n\r\n<strong>Is Internet available on the ships?</strong>\r\nMRC makes Internet available on board all our ships, but is provided by 3G networks, and a signal is not always accessible in all areas of the rivers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I use my cell phone on board the ship?</strong>\r\nThere is cell service in many places we operate, but not everywhere. Please check with your service carrier to determine what services are available to you in each country. In some countries, local phones and SIM cards can be obtained for use during your trip. Please ask your guide, program manager, or cruise manager if you need advice on where/how to obtain local service.\r\n\r\n<strong>Can special diets be accommodated?</strong>\r\nWhen advised a minimum of 45 days in advance of your cruise, most diets can be accommodated. Please contact us for information on your particular dietetic requirements.\r\n\r\n<strong>Do I need travel insurance?</strong>\r\nTravel insurance is not required to participate in a MRC cruise program, but it is highly recommended, especially when considering the remote nature of some of our programs. Policies may provide you with peace of mind that you, your luggage, your cruise investment, and even your loved ones are protected in the event that something unexpected may occur. While travel insurance is available through many sources, MRC recommends Travel Insurance Services for US and Canadian residents.\r\n\r\n<strong>Are there any luggage restrictions?</strong>\r\nIn addition to any restrictions that may be imposed by your airlines (intra-Asia flights are typically restricted to 20kg per person total limit on checked luggage), MRC recommends bringing only one checked bag per person, as the storage space in cabins is limited.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is the dress code during the cruise?</strong>\r\nWhile MRC is proud of our commitment to luxury, we do not require formal dress. Our destinations are usually warm, with some cool evenings, and it is our goal for our guests to remain. We are also committed to proper hygiene, and therefore, it is required that guests always be fully dressed, with shoes, at all times in the dining room and bar.\r\nMany temples, pagodas, and other sites on our itineraries will require guests to have their knees and shoulders covered, and may also require guests to remove their shoes.\r\n\r\n<strong>What are the tipping guidelines for my cruise?</strong>\r\nGratuities for baggage handling during transfers and at our program hotels are included in the price of your program. While tipping is a very personal matter, we suggest the following guidelines for other gratuities during your trip:\r\nShip staff &amp; crew: <strong>$13.50</strong> per person, per night (given at the end of the cruise)\r\nLocal guides: <strong>$6</strong> per person, per night (given at the end of each person\'s service)\r\nLocal transportation or transfers: <strong>$1</strong> per guest, per excursion, or <strong>$2 to $3</strong> per guest, per service for long coach transfers (given at the end of each person\'s service) please note that transportation types may vary, based on which river you are sailing\r\n\r\n<strong>Can I prepay my gratuities?</strong>\r\nUnfortunately, no. We are unable to accommodate pre-payment of gratuities at this time.', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '182-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-17 05:09:28', '2016-08-17 05:09:28', '', '182', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/uncategorized/182-revision-v1-183.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
