INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('563', '5', '2016-09-27 23:24:39', '2016-09-27 23:24:39', '<strong>MRC Luxury River Expeditions</strong>\n\nYour Chi, your Energy, your Mind Body &amp; Soul are in safe hands. Welcome to Mekong River Cruiser &amp; your fleet of Viet Cruises.\n\nWho are we and who are you ?\n\nWell to begin with, you always come first!\n\nSo we believe you to be well travelled, seasoned travellers. You have a zest for life and living the great outdoors. To explore South East Asia, at any age, is not for the faint hearted – it’s for the adventurous. Be prepared to step off the beaten track and step back in time. Welcome to Indochina.!\n\nYou are of mixed nationalities, cosmopolitan in fact and have a myriad of personal tastes, likes &amp; dislikes - all matched with your individual needs, wants and expectations of a classic Asian sojourn. Dream on… We are here, waiting to welcome you…!\n\nWho are we? We believe we are the ‘chosen ones’…. those who have chosen to attend to your personal needs, 24 hours daily, 7 days weekly. We are those East &amp; Western eclectic group of individuals who live and work harmoniously together, as a dynamic team to quite simply, look after you!\n\nTake this as another “guarantee of service”.\n\nWhat should you expect of your Vietnam and Cambodian odyssey adventure - all things that is Mekong River Cruiser.\n\nSo naturally, expect the unexpected.\n\n&nbsp;', 'About us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '174-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-09-27 23:24:39', '2016-09-27 23:24:39', '', '174', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/uncategorized/174-autosave-v1-563.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('564', '5', '2016-09-27 23:24:49', '2016-09-27 23:24:49', '<strong>MRC Luxury River Expeditions</strong>\r\n\r\nYour Chi, your Energy, your Mind Body &amp; Soul are in safe hands. Welcome to Mekong River Cruiser &amp; your fleet of Viet Cruises.\r\n\r\nWho are we and who are you ?\r\n\r\nWell to begin with, you always come first!\r\n\r\nSo we believe you to be well travelled, seasoned travellers. You have a zest for life and living the great outdoors. To explore South East Asia, at any age, is not for the faint hearted – it’s for the adventurous. Be prepared to step off the beaten track and step back in time. Welcome to Indochina.!\r\n\r\nYou are of mixed nationalities, cosmopolitan in fact and have a myriad of personal tastes, likes &amp; dislikes - all matched with your individual needs, wants and expectations of a classic Asian sojourn. Dream on… We are here, waiting to welcome you…!\r\n\r\nWho are we? We believe we are the ‘chosen ones’…. those who have chosen to attend to your personal needs, 24 hours daily, 7 days weekly. We are those East &amp; Western eclectic group of individuals who live and work harmoniously together, as a dynamic team to quite simply, look after you!\r\n\r\nTake this as another “guarantee of service”.\r\n\r\nWhat should you expect of your Vietnam and Cambodian odyssey adventure - all things that is Mekong River Cruiser.\r\n\r\nSo naturally, expect the unexpected.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'About us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '174-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-09-27 23:24:49', '2016-09-27 23:24:49', '', '174', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/uncategorized/174-revision-v1-564.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('565', '5', '2016-11-02 09:44:32', '2016-11-02 02:44:32', '….Welcome to Southern Vietnam….\n\nThe ultimate journey of exploration, along the lower Mekong, is to cruise from Saigon Port through the waterways of the famous Mekong Delta and then head north into Cambodian waters. By combining shipboard life, in elegant French colonial luxury, with discreet and fascinating shore excursions, this is the most intimate way to be ‘up close and personal’ with the people and culture of Southern Vietnam.\n\nFeed your senses. Savour the extraordinary sights, sounds, smells and tastes of remote location river cruise life. This is also a journey of sensory awareness and personal enlightenment.\n\nFor 7 nights and 8 days, your crew of young proud Cambodians &amp; Vietnamese sailors will take delicate care of all your needs, wants and expectations, every nautical mile along the way.\n\nIt’s time to cross the border between Vietnam and Cambodia. From the delta’s lush dense bountiful vegetation and the rice paddies of Vietnam’s “rice bowl”, the scenery starts to change.\n\n…..Welcome to Cambodia….\n\nEqually as exotic and by comparison to Vietnam, the plains of Cambodia open before you as we cruise upstream towards the nation’s capital of Phnom Penh. Along the riverbanks the oxen-carts plough their way along a narrow path, working the land, forever contributing to the cooperative, subsistence way of Life that is Cambodia today and yesteryear.', 'Mekong Discovery (Upstream)', 'From departure in Saigon Port, to arrival in Angkor Wat seven days later,\nyou would have a lifetime of memories, of sights and sounds, of smells and tastes that make up the fabulous Mekong Delta.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '85-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-11-02 09:44:32', '2016-11-02 02:44:32', '', '85', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/uncategorized/85-autosave-v1-565.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('566', '5', '2016-09-27 23:32:35', '2016-09-27 23:32:35', 'This sleepy backwater town is famous for Keo Dua (coconut candy). It is situated approximately ninety minutes from Saigon by road and is a riverside town linked to Can Tho by bridge or riverboat.\r\n\r\nThis shore excursion is designed to immerse guests deep within the jungle of the Mekong Delta. Strolling through the narrows paths gives you a sense of village life and community and shows typical daily life amongst the local residents.\r\n\r\nThe French Colonial influence can be seen today with classic architecture not only throughout the town, but also the outskirts.', 'Ben Tre', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ben-tre-tam-binh', '', '', '2016-11-18 05:53:34', '2016-11-17 22:53:34', '', '0', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/?post_type=port&#038;p=566', '0', 'port', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('567', '5', '2016-09-27 23:33:08', '2016-09-27 23:33:08', 'Can Tho is the epicenter of the Mekong Delta and the largest city in the region. It is traditionally the main departure point for travellers exploring the delta by waterway.\r\n\r\nThe Cai Rang floating market features in most international TV travel programs. It is the largest floating market in the region where most of the trading is done early morning, from sunrise until around 9.00am.\r\n\r\nShortly after sunrise, we board a local riverboat for a fascinating and exciting cruise through this famed floating market. The traders are selling their produce in a frenetic manner. We navigate amongst the old timber boats and witness river life Vietnam style. This location is a photographer’s dream; entirely traditional, extremely colorful and an early highlight of your Mekong River experience.', 'Can Tho', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'can-tho-thot-not', '', '', '2016-11-18 05:54:18', '2016-11-17 22:54:18', '', '0', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/?post_type=port&#038;p=567', '0', 'port', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('568', '5', '2016-09-27 23:33:26', '2016-09-27 23:33:26', 'Long Xuyen is the capital of An Giang province and prospers from agriculture, fish processing and cashew nut farms.\r\n\r\nCao Dai temple, where we learn about Caodaism, one of Vietnam’s fascinating religions. A popular movement that emerged on the early 20<sup>th</sup> century, Caodaism was a philosophy of combining the various sects and ideologies throughout Vietnam, towards the end of the French colonial period.\r\n\r\nLocated 8kms from the city center, the Long Xuyen crocodile farm boasts an internationally recognized breeding and sustainable farming program. In the afternoon we visit these notorious reptiles, up close and not too personal, and learn about their bearing on the Mekong Delta as they once inhabited these waters.', 'Long Xuyen', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'long-xuyen', '', '', '2016-11-18 05:56:00', '2016-11-17 22:56:00', '', '0', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/?post_type=port&#038;p=568', '0', 'port', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('569', '5', '2016-09-27 23:33:43', '2016-09-27 23:33:43', 'Hong Ngu is a remote island that supports a self sufficient and independent village community of around 20,000 residents. Located approximately 15kms from the Cambodian border, this island provides guests with their final insight of traditional Vietnamese lifestyle.\r\n\r\nFamed for the medieval looms, the elderly village ladies weave colorful scarves that are sent across the border to neighboring Cambodia.\r\n\r\nThe island has an unconventional pagoda where the religious followers of the Hoa Hoa sect reside. This district was once a stronghold of the ‘Hoa Hoa’ religious sect. Founded in 1939 the sect emphasizes simplicity in worship and does not believe in temples. Until 1956 ‘Hoa Hoa’ had an army and constituted a major military force in the region.', 'Hong Ngu', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hong-ngu', '', '', '2016-11-18 05:57:09', '2016-11-17 22:57:09', '', '0', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/?post_type=port&#038;p=569', '0', 'port', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('570', '5', '2016-09-27 23:33:58', '2016-09-27 23:33:58', 'Phnom Penh is the vibrant bustling capital of Cambodia. Situated at the confluence of three rivers, the mighty Mekong, the Bassac and the great Tonle Sap, the city was once considered the \'Gem\' of Indochina.\r\n\r\nIn parts, Phnom Penh exudes a provincial charm and tranquility with French colonial mansions and tree-lined boulevards amidst monumental Angkorian architecture.\r\n\r\nHere in the nations capital are numerous cultural sites. Beside the Royal Palace, the Silver Pagoda, the National Museum, the Toul Sleng Genocide Museum, the Choeng Ek Killing Fields and Wat Phnom, there are several market places selling carvings, paintings, silk, silver, gems and even antiques. The district, including the outskirts of Phnom Penh, is about 380 square kilometers and boasts a population of around two million residents.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Phnom Penh', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'phnom-penh', '', '', '2016-11-18 05:59:04', '2016-11-17 22:59:04', '', '0', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/?post_type=port&#038;p=570', '0', 'port', '', '0');
