INSERT INTO `mrc_posts` VALUES ('1101', '5', '2016-11-18 05:58:35', '2016-11-17 22:58:35', 'Phnom Penh is the vibrant bustling capital of Cambodia. Situated at the confluence of three rivers, the mighty Mekong, the Bassac and the great Tonle Sap, the city was once considered the \'Gem\' of Indochina.\n\nIn parts, Phnom Penh exudes a provincial charm and tranquility with French colonial mansions and tree-lined boulevards amidst monumental Angkorian architecture.\n\nHere in the nations capital are numerous cultural sites. Beside the Royal Palace, the Silver Pagoda, the National Museum, the Toul Sleng Genocide Museum, the Choeng Ek Killing Fields and Wat Phnom, there are several market places selling carvings, paintings, silk, silver, gems and even antiques. The district, including the outskirts of Phnom Penh, is about 380 square kilometers and boasts a population of around two million residents.\n\nFirst stop is the Royal Palace. We stroll through the beautifully landscaped palace grounds and visit the Throne Hall and Moonlight Pavilion. We encounter ancient stupas and spirit houses before witnessing the Silver Pagoda, home of the famous Emerald and Maitreya Buddha, encrusted with 9000 diamonds.\n\nReturning to the ship for lunch and to refresh, in the afternoon we journey out of town to the infamous Killing Fields of Choeung Ek.', 'Phnom Penh', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '570-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-11-18 05:58:35', '2016-11-17 22:58:35', '', '570', 'https://www.vietprincess.com/uncategorized/570-autosave-v1-1101.html', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
